<br>
Guard Leafstalker was annoyed. Today, he had lost his place as Lieutenant, and was demoted to guarding the newbie lift, of all places. No action, nobody to talk to except these puny elves running around half-naked, trying to swing their swords and kill bats. He rolled his eyes. Since when were bats a nuisance, anyway? He thought back to his demotion. He had been on duty, patrolling his route along the platforms of Kelethin, when some movement from an inn window caught his eye. Sitting at the window was a beautiful elven maiden, and she beckoned to him. How could he refuse? He entered the inn, and searched for her room. Finding it, he opened the door, and she screamed! The innkeeper arrived at once; seeing a guardsman apparently trying to force his way into a lady's room, he immediately called for the guards. And so, his reputation ruined, Lieutenant Leafstalker became Guard Leafstalker. <br>
<br>
Standing at guard duty was boring. Having an occasional swipe at a wasp or bat was hardly challenging, and he had no one to talk to. Suddenly, a wood elf came running along the path, and pressed the button for the lift as hard as he could. Leafstalker noticed that his left arm was bleeding and thought he had better be prepared for trouble.<br>
<br>
&quot;What are you running from now, elf?&quot; the guard challenged, rather insolently.<br>
<br>
&quot;None of your business,&quot; snapped the elf. &quot;You'll find out in good time.&quot; The lift arrived, and the elf stepped onto it. Pressing the button, the lift rose again, lifting him to the platform high above. Even before it had reached the platform, the elf jumped up, running as fast as he could along the swaying wooden bridges and lofty platforms of Kelethin. Coming up to a door, he knocked, opened the door, and went in. The door closed behind him. Above the door, the sign read 'Faydark's Champions'. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub39.ezboard.com/bfellowshipforlife.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lluir@fellowshipforlife>Lluir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/4/03 7:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dreams of Glory</span><hr size=1> Maesyn Trueshot, guildmaster of the rangers, was getting old. It was many years since he had seen real action, and his archery skills were no longer what they had once been. Spending his life sifting through papers, showing new rangers how to create their own bows, this was not how a ranger's life was supposed to be. But he was needed as a guildmaster, so he had accepted the task, and tried not to regret it. <br>
<br>
Deep in thought, he was startled when the door burst open and a ranger stumbled in. Seeing the elf was very pale, Maesyn immediately motioned to Samatansyn, the least senior of the rangers there, to heal the newcomer. As he was healed, he tried to give his message.<br>
<br>
&quot;Listen closely. I was in the Feerott this night. The ogres are going to war; marching on Kaladim, all of them. The Tier'Dal are also involved, one of their kind stirred up the ogres. They believe the end of the age is coming with the opening of the planes, and with the end, it will be war.&quot; Everyone gasps, Maesyn opens his mouth to question him. The ranger closes his eyes, clearly exhausted from his long run. <br>
<br>
Changing his mind, Maesyn motions the ranger to a side room to sleep. Returning to his place in the hall, the aging guildmaster declares, &quot;It has begun. Send messengers to all guilds. Let the Koada'Dal know. And send word to the dwarves. They must be warned.&quot; Without a word, rangers scurry off into the night, bearing the tidings of war. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub39.ezboard.com/bfellowshipforlife.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lluir@fellowshipforlife>Lluir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/8/03 12:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dreams of Glory</span><hr size=1> **********************************************<br>
I woke up with a pounding headache. Opening my eyes, the small wooden room swam dizzily before me. Staring up at the ceiling, I tried to focus on the intricate carvings etched into the wood, but had to give up. Stretching my arms out, I gasped at the sudden pain; clearly, my left arm was badly injured. Forcing myself to relax, I closed my eyes and tried to concentrate so I could cast a healing spell. <br>
A knock on the door interrupted my attempt at concentration, and I heard someone come in. Opening my eyes, I gazed into the face of a beautiful redheaded elf maiden. She seemed to tower over me, so I supposed she was of the Koada'Dal. <br>
&quot;Oh! You're awake already!&quot; she exclaimed, surprised. Her voice was light and melodic, perfectly charming to the ear. I almost missed what she was saying, just listening to the sound of it. &quot;How do you feel?&quot; she continued. From her mere presence, there seemed to emanate a calm tranquility that soothed my headache.<br>
&quot;Uh... a bit sore and tired, but recovering. Where am I?&quot; I was surprised at how weak my voice sounded; I must have been asleep for a week!<br>
The girl blushed a bit. &quot;In my guest room, actually. Do you not remember this place?&quot; I had no clue - I didn't even know who she was! Sensing this, she went on, &quot;You've been asleep for a month or so; the healers kept you asleep so you could heal. The dagger was poisoned, you know.&quot; The dagger? What dagger? Why couldn't I remember anything?<br>
&quot;Uh... yes, ah yes, the dagger. Did he get away?&quot; I tried to play along, supposing I must have been stabbed while guarding the forest, as my usual duty had it. I wondered who would stab me, especially with poison. She stared at me, so I trailed off, wondering what blunder I had just committed.<br>
&quot;You don't remember what happened, do you?&quot; she asked, bluntly. I shook my head. &quot;You were spying on the ogres in the Feerott, and when you were about to leave, a dark elf saw you and threw a dagger at you. You still made it here, delivered your message, and collapsed in the ranger guildhouse. No one realized how serious your wound was until the next day.&quot;<br>
&quot;Are you one of the healers, then? I am most grateful to you.&quot; I had to say something, though I was reeling in shock - how could I have forgotten all of this? What was the message I had delivered? Again, she stared at me, surprised. &quot;I'm sorry... am I supposed to know you?&quot; I asked sheepishly.<br>
&quot;The healers said the medecines would have some effect on your memory, but this is ...&quot; she trailed off. Pulling herself together, she introduced herself. &quot;I'm Leoana, of the Enchanters of Felwithe. You came to help me a few times in my training days around Kelethin. The healers had no beds to spare for you, so I offered my house. Duon comes to check on you regularly... you do remember Duon?&quot; ---unfinished <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=6.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=6.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/blueMoon/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=6.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.threadControl?topicID=6.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/blueMoon/deleteThread.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6.topic><img src=http://www.e